About
This location is our manufacturing facility and home of the Shelby Heritage Center. Visitors will see a wide variety of vehicles in the Shelby Heritage Center, from Cobras to Supersnakes and all of our current products. We also have a large merchandise store and tons of Shelby information available. Self-guided tours all the rest of the time during our scheduled hours of operation.
Duration: 1-2 hours

  • Quiggles
    Havre, Montana14 contributions
    If you like cars, please go!
    There are 2 choices - you can go in and look at the cars for free. Or, you can pay ($59, I think) to take a guided tour - this comes with a gift bag with Shelby merchandise in it. We opted for the free tour. My girls had absolutely no interest in this, but hubby, son and I really enjoyed it! Beautiful cars. Great info. Totally suggest this! If you're not into cars, there are some benches to sit on while you wait - they are inside, so out of the weather. There is a shop where you can buy Shelby merch - t-shirts were $30, so not totally outrageous. And, I'd just like to say that if any of the owners of those vehicles (some are on loan) feel generous and wanted to let me drive one of these for a little bit that would be ok with me!!

How do i get there by public transport ? Are there only shelbys on display or even other mustangs on display ?
Written May 28, 2018
LMG2
Las Vegas, Nevada
126 contributions
The SDX express, a double long bus that runs on Las Vegas Boulevard will get you there. A 24 hour pass is approximately $8. Take the bus south past Mandalay Bay to a stop near Sunset Road. You may need to get off at Town Square and walk back to Sunset. Go East on Sunset along the right side of the road. The Shelby Museum is on the right side of the bridge, along the freeway frontage road. Yes, there are many other cars on display. Pleas check their website for current operating hours.
